The '''leisure industry''' is the segment of business focused on [[recreation]], [[entertainment]], [[sports]], and [[tourism]] (REST)-related products and services (including all playable [[simulacrum|simulacra]]).

The field has developed to the point of having university degrees and disciplines focused on it, such as the [[Cornell University School of Hotel Administration]], [[Webber International University|Webber]], and [[San Jose State University]]'s departments of [[Hospitality industry|hospitality]], recreation and tourism management.<ref>[http://www.sjsu.edu/hrtm/]</ref> Some universities offer leisure degrees, two of those universities can be found in the Netherlands: the Breda University of Applied Sciences and the Stenden University of Applied Sciences. Both offer [[Bachelor's degree|bachelor]]'s in international leisure management.

