{{infobox Organization |name = National Contract Management Association |image = National Contract Management Association logo.png |image_border = |size = 200px |caption = |map = |msize = |mcaption = |abbreviation = NCMA |motto = |formation = 1959 |extinction = |type = [[Non-profit]] |status = |purpose = [[Contract management|Contract Management]] |headquarters = [[Ashburn, Virginia]] |location = [[United States]] |region_served = [[United States]] |membership = 20,000+ |language = |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = {{Official website|http://www.ncmahq.org}} |remarks = }}
The '''National Contract Management Association''' ('''NCMA''') is a [[professional association]], based in the [[United States]], dedicated to the profession of [[contract management]].<ref name="What is NCMA?">[http://www.ncmahq.org/discover-our-profession/what-is-ncma ''What is NCMA?'']</ref> Founded in 1959, NCMA now has over 20,000 members and more than 100 local chapters.<ref name="What is NCMA?"></ref><ref name="NCMA Local Chapters">[http://www.ncmahq.org/connect-with-peers/local-chapters NCMA local chapters.]</ref> NCMA promotes contract management through various means, including education, networking, publications, legislative and regulatory alerts, professional certifications, a code of ethics, awards, job postings, salary surveys, and a leadership development program. <ref name="What is NCMA?"></ref> <ref name="NCMA Local Chapters"></ref> <ref name ="NCMA Events and Education">[http://www.ncmahq.org/learn-and-advance/events-education NCMA events and education.]</ref> <ref name="NCMA Contract Management magazine">[http://www.ncmahq.org/stay-informed/contract-management-magazine NCMA ''Contract Management'' magazine.]</ref> <ref name="NCMA Publications">[http://www.ncmahq.org/stay-informed/publications NCMA publications.]</ref> <ref name="">[http://www.ncmahq.org/stay-informed/legislative-and-regulatory-alerts NCMA legislative and regulatory alerts.]</ref> <ref name="NCMA Professional Certification Program">[http://www.ncmahq.org/learn-and-advance/certification NCMA professional certification program.]</ref> <ref name="NCMA Code of Ethics">[http://www.ncmahq.org/discover-our-profession/code-of-ethics NCMA ''Code of Ethics''.]</ref> <ref name="NCMA Awards">[http://www.ncmahq.org/discover-our-profession/awards NCMA awards.]</ref> <ref name="NCMA Job Board">[http://www.ncmahq.org/discover-our-profession/career-path/jobs NCMA job board.]</ref> <ref name="NCMA Contract Management Salary Survey">[http://www.ncmahq.org/discover-our-profession/career-path/salary-survey NCMA annual ''Contract Management Salary Survey''.]</ref> <ref name="NCMA Contract Management Leadership Develop Program">[http://www.ncmahq.org/learn-and-advance/contract-management-leadership-development-program-(cmldp) NCMA ''Contract Management Leadership Development Program (CMLDP)''.]</ref>
==Certification programs== NCMA offers the following [[professional certification|professional certifications]] in contract management:<ref name="NCMA Professional Certification Program"></ref> *Certified Professional Contracts Manager (CPCM) based on demonstrating certain education, training, and experience requirements and successfully passing a comprehensive exam on a broad [[body of knowledge| body of knowledge (BOK)]] for contract management.<ref name="NCMA CPCM Certification">[http://www.ncmahq.org/learn-and-advance/certification/cpcm NCMA ''Certified Professional Contracts Manager'' (''CPCM'') certification.]</ref> *Certified Federal Contracts Manager (CFCM), previously Certified Associate Contracts Manager (CACM), based on demonstrating certain education, training, and experience requirements and successfully passing a comprehensive exam on the [[Federal Acquisition Regulation|Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR)]].<ref name="NCMA CFCM Certification">[http://www.ncmahq.org/learn-and-advance/certification/cfcm NCMA ''Certified Federal Contracts Manager'' (''CFCM'') certification.]</ref> *Certified Commercial Contracts Manager (CCCM) based on demonstrating certain education, training, and experience requirements and successfully passing a comprehensive exam [[Uniform Commercial Code|Uniform Commercial Code (UCC)]].<ref name="NCMA CCCM Certification">[http://www.ncmahq.org/learn-and-advance/certification/cccm NCMA ''Certified Commercial Contracts Manager'' (''CCCM'') certification.]</ref>
==Publications== NCMA produces the following contract management publications:<ref name="NCMA Publications"></ref> * '''Contract Management'''<ref name="NCMA Contract Management magazine"></ref> * '''Journal of Contract Management'''<ref name="NCMA Journal of Contract Management">[http://www.ncmahq.org/stay-informed/publications/journal-of-contract-management NCMA ''Journal of Contract Management''.]</ref> * '''Contract Management News'''<ref name="NCMA Contract Management News">[http://www.ncmahq.org/stay-informed/publications/contract-management-newsletter ''NCMA Contract Management News'' e-newsletter.]</ref> * '''Annual Review of Government Contracting'''<ref name="NCMA Annual Review of Government Contracting">[http://www.ncmahq.org/learn-and-advance/ncma-books NCMA annual ''Review of Government Contracting''.]</ref> * '''Annual Contract Management Salary Survey'''<ref name="NCMA Contract Management Salary Survey"></ref> * '''Contract Management Body of Knowledge''' ('''CMBOK''')<ref name="NCMA CMBOK">[http://www.ncmahq.org/learn-and-advance/ncma-books NCMA ''Contract Management Body of Knowledge'' (''CMBOK'').]</ref> * '''Desktop Guide to Basic Contracting Terms'''<ref name="NCMA Desktop Guide">[http://www.ncmahq.org/learn-and-advance/ncma-books NCMA ''Desktop Guide to Basic Contracting Terms''.]</ref>
